            <description><![CDATA[
<h2>What's New</h2>

<h3>Fixed</h3>
<ul>
<li>Codex 5-hour and weekly windows now read **live** usage from the ChatGPT backend (`/wham/usage`) using the `~/.codex/auth.json` token, instead of stale local rollout logs. Usage consumed via OpenCode/ChatGPT is now reflected, fixing the menu bar showing **0%** when the local Codex CLI logs were stale. On any error the Codex column is hidden rather than showing a fabricated 0%.</li>
</ul>

See <a href="https://github.com/tartinerlabs/ClaudeMeter/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md">CHANGELOG.md</a> for full details.
            ]]></description>
